    <Statements>
      <Statement>Explaining why multiplying a given number by a fraction greater than 1 results in a product greater than the given number (recognizing multiplication by whole numbers greater than 1 as a familiar case); explaining why multiplying a given number by a fraction less than 1 results in a product smaller than the given number; and relating the principle of fraction equivalence &lt;i&gt;a&lt;/i&gt;/&lt;i&gt;b&lt;/i&gt; = (&lt;i&gt;n&lt;/i&gt; &amp;times; &lt;i&gt;a&lt;/i&gt;)/(&lt;i&gt;n&lt;/i&gt; &amp;times; &lt;i&gt;b&lt;/i&gt;) to the effect of multiplying &lt;i&gt;a&lt;/i&gt;/&lt;i&gt;b&lt;/i&gt; by 1.</Statement>
